        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 8:09PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 808 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Porter Springs, or near
Dahlonega. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Winds up to 40 mph, pea sized hail and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Camp Coleman Lake, Suches, Camp Merrill, Porter Springs, Turners
Corner, Nimblewill, Dahlonega, Woods Hole Shelter, Blood Mountain
Shelter, and Gooch Mountain Shelter.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. Motorists should
slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
